storybook v3.2.14 / v3.2.15

We encountered two different characteristics of this defect:

* Adding two stories using the same component name (e.g. 'Container', see example) in the same file or in different files leads to the following error: "Attempted to redefine property 'Container'." Reloading usually results in the case described below.

```
storiesOf('Test1', module)
    .add('story 1', () => {
        class Container extends React.Component {
            public render(): JSX.Element {
                return <Text>Test</Text>;
            }
        }
        return <Container />;
    })
    .add('story 2', () => {
        class Container extends React.Component {
            public render(): JSX.Element {
                return <Text>Test</Text>;
            }
        }
        return <Container />;
    });
```

* Adding multiple stories using the same component name in the same file or in different files leads to a blank screen and high CPU load without showing any errors at all. After a few seconds the app is not responding anymore.

In wiki page on storybook decorators, the example code is wrong:

```
const CenterDecorator = ({ children }) => (
  <div style={styles}>
    { children }
  </div>
);

storiesOf('Button', module)
  .addDecorator(CenterDecorator)
  .add('with text', () => (
    <Button onClick={action('clicked')}>Hello Button</Button>
  ))
```

this should be:
```
const CenterDecorator = (storyFn) => (
  <div style={styles}>
    { storyFn() }
  </div>
);
```

